Welcome To Triaxis GNU/Linux Handbook AMD64
This Guide Will Help You To Install Triaxis Correctly

1 Download Arch Linux ISO Here https://fastly.mirror.pkgbuild.com/iso/2026.03.01/
2 Flash Arch Linux ISO Using Etcher
3 Follow The Installation Guide https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Installation_guide Or Archinstall
4 Linux Filesystem Must Ext4
5 Bootloader Must Be GRUB
6 Desktop Environment Must Be KDE Plasma GNOME Or XFCE Or Base Or Sway Tiling WM
7 Audio Must Pipewire
8 Network Configuration Must Be NetworkManager
9 After You Install Login To Desktop
10 Open Terminal Then Run sudo pacman -Syu
11 Run sudo nano /etc/os-release
   Then Change NAME= And PREETY_NAME= To Triaxis GNU/Linux
   Change ID=arch To ID=triaxis
   Change HOME_URL"https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Triaxis-GNU-Linux"
12 Run sudo pacman -S firefox
13 Go To https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Triaxis-GNU-Linux then download triaxis logo on top beginning at readme
14 Save The Image Then Name It To triaxis-logo.png then save it to download
15 Then run sudo mv /home/yourusername/Downloads/triaxis-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps
16 Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/triaxis-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/archlinux-logo.png
17 Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/triaxis-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/archlinux-logo.svg
18 Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/triaxis-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/archlinux-logo-text.svg
19 Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/triaxis-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/archlinux-logo-text-dark.svg
20 Then sudo nano /etc/os-release
21 Then Change LOGO=archlinux-logo To LOGO=/usr/share/pixmaps/triaxis-logo.png
22 Run sudo nano /etc/default/grub
23 Then Change GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR="Arch" To GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR="Triaxis"
24 Update Grub Using sudo grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg
25 Run sudo nano /etc/grub.d/10_linux
26 If You See OS=Linux Change OS=Linux To OS=GNU/Linux And OS="${GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR} GNU/Linux"
27 Update Grub Using sudo grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg
28 Run sudo nano /etc/default/grub
29 Then Change GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="loglevel 3 quiet" To GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT=""
30 Update Grub Using sudo grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg
31 Scroll Down TO Triaxis Official Artwork Theme Slasher Then Download This Picture Then Name It To Slasher.jpg Then Save It To Download
32 Then Create Folder Name Slasher On Download Then Move Slasher.jpg To Slasher Folder
33 Run sudo mv /home/yourusername/Downloads/Slasher /usr/share/wallpapers/
34 Right Click And Click Desktop And Wallpaper Then Find Slasher Then After Find Slasher Select Slasher Then Click OK
35 Go To System Settings Then Notifications Then Configure For System... Then Find Login And Logout Sound Then Click Play a sound on Login And Logout Then Click Apply

36 Have Fun And Start Using Triaxis GNU/Linux AMD64
